---
name: tts-chutes
description: Text-to-speech using Chutes Kokoro API (Kokoro-82M v1.0). Use when the user needs to convert text to audio, create voiceovers, read content aloud, or generate speech files. Triggers include requests to "speak this", "read aloud", "convert to audio", "generate voice", "TTS", or any task requiring text-to-speech synthesis.
allowed-tools: Bash
---

# Text-to-Speech with Chutes Kokoro

Kokoro-82M v1.0 — 82M parameter open-weight TTS model. 54 voces en 9 idiomas.

## Core Workflow

1. **Generate speech**: Use `tts-speak` to convert text to audio
2. **Output options**: Play directly, save to file, or pipe to other tools
3. **Customize**: Adjust voice, speed, and format as needed

## Basic Usage

```bash
# Simple speak (plays audio directly)
tts-speak "Hello, this is a test."

# Save to file (no playback)
tts-speak "Hello, this is a test." --output speech.mp3

# Save to file with custom voice
tts-speak "Bonjour, ceci est un test." --voice af_bella --output greeting.mp3

# Adjust speed (0.5 = half speed, 2.0 = double speed)
tts-speak "Speaking slowly." --speed 0.5 --output slow.mp3
tts-speak "Speaking quickly." --speed 1.5 --output fast.mp3
```

## Command Options

```bash
tts-speak <text> [options]

Options:
  --output <file>     Save audio to file instead of playing
  --voice <voice>     Voice ID (default: af_heart)
  --speed <number>    Speech speed 0.5-2.0 (default: 1.0)
  --quiet             Output to stdout (for piping)
  --help              Show help message

Note: API returns WAV/PCM audio (24kHz, mono). File extension doesn't affect format.
```

## Available Voices

Quality grades (A-F) según el dataset original de Kokoro. Voces marcadas como **★** son las mejores.

### 🇺🇸 American English (11F, 9M)
`lang_code='a'` — Usar con texto en inglés americano.

| Voz | Género | Calidad | Descripción |
|-----|--------|---------|-------------|
| `af_heart` ★ | 🚺 | **A** | Cálida, amigable — la mejor voz general |
| `af_bella` ★ | 🚺 | **A-** | Clara, profesional — ideal para presentaciones |
| `af_nicole` | 🚺 | B- | Expresiva, buena para narración larga |
| `af_aoede` | 🚺 | C+ | Dulce, suave |
