## Cómo elegir voz según el idioma

1. **Detectar el idioma del texto** del usuario
2. **Usar el prefijo correcto**:

| Idioma | Prefijo | Mejor voz |
|--------|---------|-----------|
| Inglés (EEUU) | `af_` / `am_` | `af_heart`, `af_bella` |
| Inglés (UK) | `bf_` / `bm_` | `bf_emma` |
| Japonés | `jf_` / `jm_` | `jf_alpha` |
| Chino | `zf_` / `zm_` | `zf_xiaobei` |
| Español | `ef_` / `em_` | `ef_dora` |
| Francés | `ff_` | `ff_siwis` |
| Hindi | `hf_` / `hm_` | `hf_alpha` |
| Italiano | `if_` / `im_` | `if_sara` |
| Portugués BR | `pf_` / `pm_` | `pf_dora` |

3. **Elegir género**: prefijo `f` = femenino, `m` = masculino
4. **Calidad**: preferir voces con grado más alto (A > B > C > D)

## Common Patterns

### Read Aloud Content

```bash
# Read a message
tts-speak "Your build completed successfully."

# Read file contents
tts-speak "$(cat article.txt)" --output article.mp3

# Read with custom pacing
tts-speak "Important announcement. Please listen carefully." --speed 0.8
```

### Generate Audio Files

```bash
# Create voiceover for video
tts-speak "Welcome to our tutorial series." --voice am_michael --output intro.mp3

# Generate multiple segments
tts-speak "Chapter one: Getting Started." --output ch1.mp3
tts-speak "Chapter two: Installation." --output ch2.mp3
tts-speak "Chapter three: Configuration." --output ch3.mp3

# Create audio in different formats
tts-speak "High quality audio." --format flac --output hq.flac
tts-speak "Web optimized." --format mp3 --output web.mp3
```

### Pipeline Integration

```bash
# Pipe to ffmpeg for processing
tts-speak "Text content" --quiet | ffmpeg -i pipe:0 -ar 44100 output.wav

# Chain with other audio tools
tts-speak "Announcement" --quiet | sox -t mp3 - -t wav announcement.wav

# Combine multiple TTS segments
tts-speak "Part one" --quiet > combined.mp3
tts-speak "Part two" --quiet >> combined.mp3
```

### Accessibility & Notifications

```bash
# System notification
tts-speak "Battery low. Please connect charger." --voice af_bella

# Reading long content in chunks
tts-speak "$(head -n 50 document.txt)" --output doc_part1.mp3
tts-speak "$(tail -n +51 document.txt)" --output doc_part2.mp3

# Quick pronunciation check
tts-speak "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog." --speed 0.7
```

## Shell Command

The `tts-speak` command is installed at `~/.local/bin/tts-speak`:

```bash
# Play audio directly
tts-speak "Hello world"

# Save to file
tts-speak "Hello world" --output speech.mp3

# Custom voice and speed
tts-speak "Hello world" --voice am_michael --speed 0.9 --output greeting.mp3

# Pipe to other tools
tts-speak "Hello world" --quiet | ffmpeg -i pipe:0 output.wav
```

## Shell Function (alternative for playback only)

Add to your shell config for quick playback without saving:

```bash
speak() {
    curl -s -X POST https://chutes-kokoro.chutes.ai/speak \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $CHUTES_API_TOKEN" \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d "{\"text\": \"$*\", \"speed\": 1, \"voice\": \"af_heart\"}" | \
        ffplay -nodisp -autoexit -loglevel error -i pipe:0
}

# Usage: speak "Hello world"
```

## Error Handling

```bash
# Check API token is set
if [ -z "$CHUTES_API_TOKEN" ]; then
    echo "Error: CHUTES_API_TOKEN not set"
    exit 1
fi

# Retry on failure
tts-speak "Important message" --output msg.mp3 || \
    tts-speak "Important message" --output msg.mp3
```

## Best Practices

1. **Elegir voz por idioma**: Usa el prefijo correcto según el idioma del texto
2. **Calidad over cantidad**: Prefiere voces con grado A o B sobre las D
3. **Texto corto**: Textos de 100-200 tokens funcionan mejor
4. **Ajustar velocidad**: 0.9-1.0 para narración, 0.7-0.8 para texto complejo
5. **Cachear audio**: Reusa archivos generados para contenido repetido
6. **Probar antes**: Verifica voz y velocidad con una muestra corta

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| No audio playback | Check ffplay is installed (`brew install ffmpeg`) |
| API error 401 | Verify `CHUTES_API_TOKEN` is set and valid |
| Audio cuts off | Text may be too long; split into segments |
| Wrong voice | Check voice ID spelling; see available voices table |
| Slow generation | Reduce text length or check network connection |
| Voice suena mal | Usar una voz con mejor grado de calidad (A > B > C > D) |

## Examples

```bash
# English narration
tts-speak "Welcome to this tutorial." --voice af_heart --output intro_en.mp3

# Spanish voiceover
tts-speak "Bienvenidos a este tutorial." --voice ef_dora --output intro_es.mp3

# French narration
tts-speak "Bienvenue dans ce tutoriel." --voice ff_siwis --output intro_fr.mp3

# Japanese
tts-speak "こんにちは、ようこそ。" --voice jf_alpha --output intro_ja.mp3

# Chinese
tts-speak "欢迎来到本教程。" --voice zf_xiaobei --output intro_zh.mp3

# Hindi
tts-speak "इस ट्यूटोरियल में आपका स्वागत है।" --voice hf_alpha --output intro_hi.mp3

# Italian
tts-speak "Benvenuti a questo tutorial." --voice if_sara --output intro_it.mp3

# Brazilian Portuguese
tts-speak "Bem-vindo a este tutorial." --voice pf_dora --output intro_pt.mp3

# British English
tts-speak "Welcome to this tutorial." --voice bf_emma --output intro_uk.mp3

# Multilingual greeting set
for lang in "en:af_heart:Hello" "es:ef_dora:Hola" "fr:ff_siwis:Bonjour" "ja:jf_alpha:こんにちは" "zh:zf_xiaobei:你好" "hi:hf_alpha:नमस्ते"; do
  IFS=":" read -r lang_code voice text <<< "$lang"
  tts-speak "$text" --voice "$voice" --output "greeting_${lang_code}.mp3"
done
```
